&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whipps Cross Hospital NHS Trust - Theatres &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5, Theatre Practioner - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barts NHS Trust is the largest trust in the country. Our mission is to provide excellent healthcare for our patients through excellence in research, education and training. We are passionate about the quality of care we deliver and are looking for staff who can be developed and align with the Trusts Vision and Values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We at Whipps Cross Theatres are looking to recruit into Band 5 Theatre Scrub Practioner roles. Candidates should have 6 months post qualification experience. Once in post candidates will be supported through a recognised Induction Programme and encouraged to complete the Theatre Course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Theatres have undergone an extensive re-development progamme, We are currently undertaking an extensive Elective Surgery Recovery programme , post COVID.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Theatre Adult and Paediatric casemix is challenging and specialities include: Upper and Lower GI, Urology, Maxillofacial , Head and Neck, ENT, Gynaecology, Orthopaedics and Trauma, Paediatric Surgery and Day Surgery. As well as a busy 24 hour Emergency Theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Theatre teams are passionate getting it right for patients and their families and in order to achieve this we are looking to appoint enthusiastic, motivated and dynamic individuals. Once appointed you will be developed over the following12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact –&lt;/p&gt;
